-- Romania Utility Awards Water Contract to Italian Company
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-03-25T12:19:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-25/romania-utility-awards-water-contract-to-italian-company.html
The Romanian utility  Cia de Apa
Oltenia SA  awarded a 36.1 million-lei ($11 million) contract for
water-treatment plant improvements to the Italian construction
company Ercole Marelli Impianti Tecnologici SpA.   The utility received six bids for the contract, which
includes upgrading a water-treatment plant in the southern town
of Isalnita, according to a  European Union notice . The bid was
initially valued at 40.8 million lei, according to the notice.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  